{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":388,"text":"As it turns out, when tens of millions\nof people are unemployed"},{"time":3992,"text":"or underemployed,"},{"time":5550,"text":"there's a fair amount of interest\nin what technology might be doing"},{"time":8740,"text":"to the labor force."},{"time":9926,"text":"And as I look at the conversation,"},{"time":11839,"text":"it strikes me that it's focused\non exactly the right topic,"},{"time":15543,"text":"and at the same time,\nit's missing the point entirely."},{"time":18392,"text":"The topic that it's focused on,"},{"time":19957,"text":"the question is whether or not all these\ndigital technologies are affecting"},{"time":24464,"text":"people's ability to earn a living,"},{"time":26505,"text":"or, to say it a little bit different way,"},{"time":28514,"text":"are the droids taking our jobs?"},{"time":30627,"text":"And there's some evidence that they are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32588,"text":"The Great Recession ended\nwhen American GDP resumed"},{"time":36657,"text":"its kind of slow, steady march upward,"},{"time":39548,"text":"and some other economic indicators\nalso started to rebound,"},{"time":42842,"text":"and they got kind of healthy\nkind of quickly."},{"time":45159,"text":"Corporate profits are quite high;"},{"time":47350,"text":"in fact, if you include bank profits,"},{"time":49270,"text":"they're higher than they've ever been."},{"time":51285,"text":"And business investment\nin gear -- in equipment"},{"time":54796,"text":"and hardware and software --\nis at an all-time high."},{"time":57664,"text":"So the businesses are getting\nout their checkbooks."},{"time":61003,"text":"What they're not really doing is hiring."},{"time":63401,"text":"So this red line"},{"time":64576,"text":"is the employment-to-population ratio,"},{"time":67138,"text":"in other words, the percentage\nof working-age people in America"},{"time":71291,"text":"who have work."},{"time":72701,"text":"And we see that it cratered\nduring the Great Recession,"},{"time":75831,"text":"and it hasn't started\nto bounce back at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78752,"text":"But the story is not\njust a recession story."},{"time":81695,"text":"The decade that we've\njust been through had"},{"time":83799,"text":"relatively anemic job growth\nall throughout,"},{"time":87036,"text":"especially when we compare it\nto other decades,"},{"time":89683,"text":"and the 2000s are the only time\nwe have on record"},{"time":92737,"text":"where there were fewer people working\nat the end of the decade"},{"time":96293,"text":"than at the beginning."},{"time":97719,"text":"This is not what you want to see."},{"time":99724,"text":"When you graph the number\nof potential employees"},{"time":103131,"text":"versus the number of jobs in the country,"},{"time":105711,"text":"you see the gap gets bigger\nand bigger over time,"},{"time":109585,"text":"and then, during the Great Recession,\nit opened up in a huge way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112919,"text":"I did some quick calculations."},{"time":114403,"text":"I took the last 20 years of GDP growth"},{"time":116859,"text":"and the last 20 years\nof labor-productivity growth"},{"time":120155,"text":"and used those in a fairly\nstraightforward way"},{"time":122897,"text":"to try to project how many jobs\nthe economy was going to need"},{"time":125944,"text":"to keep growing,"},{"time":127271,"text":"and this is the line that I came up with."},{"time":129420,"text":"Is that good or bad?"},{"time":131186,"text":"This is the government's projection"},{"time":133121,"text":"for the working-age\npopulation going forward."},{"time":136481,"text":"So if these predictions are accurate,\nthat gap is not going to close."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141603,"text":"The problem is, I don't think\nthese projections are accurate."},{"time":144653,"text":"In particular, I think my projection\nis way too optimistic,"},{"time":148156,"text":"because when I did it,"},{"time":149627,"text":"I was assuming that the future\nwas kind of going to look like the past,"},{"time":153869,"text":"with labor productivity growth,"},{"time":155562,"text":"and that's actually not what I believe."},{"time":157457,"text":"Because when I look around,"},{"time":158830,"text":"I think that we ain't seen nothing yet"},{"time":161074,"text":"when it comes to technology's\nimpact on the labor force."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164702,"text":"Just in the past couple years,\nwe've seen digital tools"},{"time":168697,"text":"display skills and abilities\nthat they never, ever had before,"},{"time":172954,"text":"and that kind of eat deeply\ninto what we human beings"},{"time":176488,"text":"do for a living."},{"time":177794,"text":"Let me give you a couple examples."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179744,"text":"Throughout all of history,"},{"time":181020,"text":"if you wanted something translated\nfrom one language into another,"},{"time":184594,"text":"you had to involve a human being."},{"time":186670,"text":"Now we have multi-language, instantaneous,"},{"time":189822,"text":"automatic translation services\navailable for free"},{"time":194266,"text":"via many of our devices,\nall the way down to smartphones."},{"time":197433,"text":"And if any of us have used these,"},{"time":199253,"text":"we know that they're not perfect,\nbut they're decent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203280,"text":"Throughout all of history,\nif you wanted something written,"},{"time":206276,"text":"a report or an article,\nyou had to involve a person."},{"time":210158,"text":"Not anymore."},{"time":211335,"text":"This is an article that appeared\nin Forbes online a while back,"},{"time":214332,"text":"about Apple's earnings."},{"time":215532,"text":"It was written by an algorithm."},{"time":217720,"text":"And it's not decent -- it's perfect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221749,"text":"A lot of people look at this and they say,"},{"time":223802,"text":"\"OK, but those are very\nspecific, narrow tasks,"},{"time":226131,"text":"and most knowledge workers\nare actually generalists."},{"time":229066,"text":"And what they do is sit on top of a very\nlarge body of expertise and knowledge"},{"time":233282,"text":"and they use that to react on the fly\nto kind of unpredictable demands,"},{"time":237103,"text":"and that's very, very hard to automate.\""},{"time":239803,"text":"One of the most impressive\nknowledge workers in recent memory"},{"time":242732,"text":"is a guy named Ken Jennings."},{"time":244277,"text":"He won the quiz show\n\"Jeopardy!\" 74 times in a row."},{"time":249610,"text":"Took home three million dollars."},{"time":251824,"text":"That's Ken on the right,\ngetting beat three-to-one"},{"time":255619,"text":"by Watson, the Jeopardy-playing\nsupercomputer from IBM."},{"time":260642,"text":"So when we look at what technology can do\nto general knowledge workers,"},{"time":264181,"text":"I start to think there might not be\nsomething so special"},{"time":267283,"text":"about this idea of a generalist,"},{"time":269075,"text":"particularly when we start doing things\nlike hooking Siri up to Watson,"},{"time":273429,"text":"and having technologies\nthat can understand what we're saying"},{"time":276722,"text":"and repeat speech back to us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278730,"text":"Now, Siri is far from perfect,\nand we can make fun of her flaws,"},{"time":282657,"text":"but we should also keep in mind"},{"time":284180,"text":"that if technologies like Siri and Watson\nimprove along a Moore's law trajectory,"},{"time":289568,"text":"which they will,"},{"time":291114,"text":"in six years, they're not going to be two\ntimes better or four times better,"},{"time":294728,"text":"they'll be 16 times better\nthan they are right now."},{"time":298222,"text":"So I start to think a lot of knowledge\nwork is going to be affected by this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":302092,"text":"And digital technologies are not\njust impacting knowledge work,"},{"time":305852,"text":"they're starting to flex their muscles\nin the physical world as well."},{"time":309615,"text":"I had the chance a little while back\nto ride in the Google autonomous car,"},{"time":313364,"text":"which is as cool as it sounds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":315665,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":317877,"text":"And I will vouch that it handled\nthe stop-and-go traffic on US 101"},{"time":322322,"text":"very smoothly."},{"time":323599,"text":"There are about three and a half million\npeople who drive trucks for a living"},{"time":327274,"text":"in the United States;"},{"time":328449,"text":"I think some of them are going\nto be affected by this technology."},{"time":331541,"text":"And right now, humanoid robots\nare still incredibly primitive."},{"time":334665,"text":"They can't do very much."},{"time":336646,"text":"But they're getting better quite quickly"},{"time":338642,"text":"and DARPA, which is the investment arm\nof the Defense Department,"},{"time":342203,"text":"is trying to accelerate their trajectory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344204,"text":"So, in short, yeah, the droids\nare coming for our jobs."},{"time":349845,"text":"In the short term, we can\nstimulate job growth"},{"time":352761,"text":"by encouraging entrepreneurship"},{"time":354922,"text":"and by investing in infrastructure,"},{"time":356860,"text":"because the robots today\nstill aren't very good at fixing bridges."},{"time":360422,"text":"But in the not-too-long-term,"},{"time":362344,"text":"I think within the lifetimes\nof most of the people in this room,"},{"time":366270,"text":"we're going to transition into an economy\nthat is very productive,"},{"time":369842,"text":"but that just doesn't need\na lot of human workers."},{"time":372760,"text":"And managing that transition\nis going to be the greatest challenge"},{"time":375896,"text":"that our society faces."},{"time":377458,"text":"Voltaire summarized why; he said,"},{"time":379432,"text":"\"Work saves us from three great evils:\nboredom, vice and need.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":385170,"text":"But despite this challenge --"},{"time":387251,"text":"personally, I'm still\na huge digital optimist,"},{"time":390187,"text":"and I am supremely confident"},{"time":392415,"text":"that the digital technologies\nthat we're developing now"},{"time":395027,"text":"are going to take us\ninto a Utopian future,"},{"time":397701,"text":"not a dystopian future."},{"time":399437,"text":"And to explain why,"},{"time":400612,"text":"I want to pose a ridiculously\nbroad question."},{"time":403215,"text":"I want to ask:"},{"time":404390,"text":"what have been the most important\ndevelopments in human history?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":407760,"text":"Now, I want to share some\nof the answers that I've gotten"},{"time":410745,"text":"in response to this question."},{"time":412166,"text":"It's a wonderful question to ask\nand start an endless debate about,"},{"time":415358,"text":"because some people are going to bring up"},{"time":417356,"text":"systems of philosophy\nin both the West and the East"},{"time":420680,"text":"that have changed how a lot\nof people think about the world."},{"time":423927,"text":"And then other people will say,"},{"time":425444,"text":"\"No, actually, the big stories,\nthe big developments"},{"time":427929,"text":"are the founding\nof the world's major religions,"},{"time":430536,"text":"which have changed civilizations\nand have changed and influenced"},{"time":433786,"text":"how countless people\nare living their lives.\""},{"time":436404,"text":"And then some other folk will say,"},{"time":438125,"text":"\"Actually, what changes civilizations,"},{"time":440539,"text":"what modifies them and what changes\npeople's lives are empires,"},{"time":445348,"text":"so the great developments in human history"},{"time":447777,"text":"are stories of conquest and of war.\""},{"time":450563,"text":"And then some cheery soul\nusually always pipes up and says,"},{"time":453368,"text":"\"Hey, don't forget about plagues!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":455074,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":459007,"text":"There are some optimistic\nanswers to this question,"},{"time":461554,"text":"so some people will bring up\nthe Age of Exploration"},{"time":463992,"text":"and the opening up of the world."},{"time":465561,"text":"Others will talk about intellectual\nachievements in disciplines like math"},{"time":469363,"text":"that have helped us get\na better handle on the world,"},{"time":471881,"text":"and other folk will talk about periods\nwhen there was a deep flourishing"},{"time":475345,"text":"of the arts and sciences."},{"time":476974,"text":"So this debate will go on and on."},{"time":478585,"text":"It's an endless debate"},{"time":480070,"text":"and there's no conclusive,\nsingle answer to it."},{"time":483327,"text":"But if you're a geek like me,"},{"time":484868,"text":"you say, \"Well, what do the data say?\""},{"time":487573,"text":"And you start to do things"},{"time":488929,"text":"like graph things\nthat we might be interested in --"},{"time":491637,"text":"the total worldwide\npopulation, for example,"},{"time":494740,"text":"or some measure of social development"},{"time":497129,"text":"or the state of advancement of a society."},{"time":499641,"text":"And you start to plot the data,\nbecause, by this approach,"},{"time":503788,"text":"the big stories, the big\ndevelopments in human history,"},{"time":506417,"text":"are the ones that will bend\nthese curves a lot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508951,"text":"So when you do this\nand when you plot the data,"},{"time":511195,"text":"you pretty quickly come\nto some weird conclusions."},{"time":513911,"text":"You conclude, actually,"},{"time":515331,"text":"that none of these things\nhave mattered very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":517918,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":521980,"text":"They haven't done\na darn thing to the curves."},{"time":525357,"text":"There has been one story,\none development in human history"},{"time":530071,"text":"that bent the curve,\nbent it just about 90 degrees,"},{"time":533304,"text":"and it is a technology story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":535963,"text":"The steam engine and the other\nassociated technologies"},{"time":538757,"text":"of the Industrial Revolution"},{"time":540812,"text":"changed the world and influenced\nhuman history so much,"},{"time":544112,"text":"that in the words\nof the historian Ian Morris,"},{"time":546538,"text":"\"... they made mockery out of all\nthat had come before.\""},{"time":550353,"text":"And they did this by infinitely\nmultiplying the power of our muscles,"},{"time":553904,"text":"overcoming the limitations of our muscles."},{"time":556322,"text":"Now, what we're in the middle of now"},{"time":558844,"text":"is overcoming the limitations\nof our individual brains"},{"time":561901,"text":"and infinitely multiplying\nour mental power."},{"time":564836,"text":"How can this not be as big a deal"},{"time":568037,"text":"as overcoming the limitations\nof our muscles?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":570765,"text":"So at the risk of repeating\nmyself a little bit,"},{"time":573649,"text":"when I look at what's going on\nwith digital technology these days,"},{"time":577426,"text":"we are not anywhere near\nthrough with this journey."},{"time":580560,"text":"And when I look at what is happening\nto our economies and our societies,"},{"time":584090,"text":"my single conclusion is that\nwe ain't seen nothing yet."},{"time":587203,"text":"The best days are really ahead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588953,"text":"Let me give you a couple examples."},{"time":590978,"text":"Economies don't run on energy."},{"time":593375,"text":"They don't run on capital,\nthey don't run on labor."},{"time":596438,"text":"Economies run on ideas."},{"time":598867,"text":"So the work of innovation,\nthe work of coming up with new ideas,"},{"time":602232,"text":"is some of the most powerful, most\nfundamental work that we can do"},{"time":605954,"text":"in an economy."},{"time":607129,"text":"And this is kind of how\nwe used to do innovation."},{"time":610271,"text":"We'd find a bunch of fairly\nsimilar-looking people ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":613271,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":616791,"text":"We'd take them out of elite institutions,"},{"time":618808,"text":"we'd put them into other\nelite institutions"},{"time":620911,"text":"and we'd wait for the innovation."},{"time":622521,"text":"Now --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":623714,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":626167,"text":"as a white guy who spent\nhis whole career at MIT and Harvard,"},{"time":629679,"text":"I've got no problem with this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":631729,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":635345,"text":"But some other people do,"},{"time":636576,"text":"and they've kind of crashed the party"},{"time":638385,"text":"and loosened up\nthe dress code of innovation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":640554,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":641610,"text":"So here are the winners of a Topcoder\nprogramming challenge,"},{"time":644834,"text":"and I assure you that nobody cares"},{"time":647550,"text":"where these kids grew up,\nwhere they went to school,"},{"time":651330,"text":"or what they look like."},{"time":652854,"text":"All anyone cares about is the quality\nof the work, the quality of the ideas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":656721,"text":"And over and over again,\nwe see this happening"},{"time":658981,"text":"in the technology-facilitated world."},{"time":661529,"text":"The work of innovation\nis becoming more open,"},{"time":664050,"text":"more inclusive, more transparent\nand more merit-based,"},{"time":667723,"text":"and that's going to continue no matter\nwhat MIT and Harvard think of it,"},{"time":671445,"text":"and I couldn't be happier\nabout that development."}]},{"cues":[{"time":674349,"text":"I hear once in a while,\n\"OK, I'll grant you that,"},{"time":676828,"text":"but technology is still a tool\nfor the rich world,"},{"time":679871,"text":"and what's not happening,"},{"time":681294,"text":"these digital tools are not\nimproving the lives"},{"time":683929,"text":"of people at the bottom of the pyramid.\""},{"time":686102,"text":"And I want to say to that\nvery clearly: nonsense."},{"time":688792,"text":"The bottom of the pyramid is benefiting\nhugely from technology."},{"time":692309,"text":"The economist Robert Jensen\ndid this wonderful study a while back"},{"time":695893,"text":"where he watched, in great detail,"},{"time":697850,"text":"what happened to the fishing\nvillages of Kerala, India,"},{"time":701492,"text":"when they got mobile phones\nfor the very first time."},{"time":704397,"text":"And when you write for the Quarterly\nJournal of Economics,"},{"time":707230,"text":"you have to use very dry\nand very circumspect language."},{"time":710136,"text":"But when I read his paper,"},{"time":711422,"text":"I kind of feel Jensen\nis trying to scream at us"},{"time":713653,"text":"and say, \"Look, this was a big deal."},{"time":716001,"text":"Prices stabilized, so people\ncould plan their economic lives."},{"time":719676,"text":"Waste was not reduced --\nit was eliminated."},{"time":723747,"text":"And the lives of both\nthe buyers and the sellers"},{"time":726012,"text":"in these villages measurably improved.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":728813,"text":"Now, what I don't think\nis that Jensen got extremely lucky"},{"time":732627,"text":"and happened to land\nin the one set of villages"},{"time":734862,"text":"where technology made things better."},{"time":737195,"text":"What happened instead\nis he very carefully documented"},{"time":739866,"text":"what happens over and over again\nwhen technology comes for the first time"},{"time":743969,"text":"to an environment and a community:"},{"time":745930,"text":"the lives of people, the welfares\nof people, improve dramatically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":749791,"text":"So as I look around at all the evidence"},{"time":751696,"text":"and I think about the room\nthat we have ahead of us,"},{"time":754157,"text":"I become a huge digital optimist"},{"time":756009,"text":"and I start to think that this wonderful\nstatement from the physicist Freeman Dyson"},{"time":760609,"text":"is actually not hyperbole."},{"time":762371,"text":"This is an accurate assessment\nof what's going on."},{"time":764904,"text":"Our technologies are great gifts,"},{"time":767626,"text":"and we, right now,\nhave the great good fortune"},{"time":770697,"text":"to be living at a time when\ndigital technology is flourishing,"},{"time":774451,"text":"when it is broadening and deepening\nand becoming more profound"},{"time":777870,"text":"all around the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":779172,"text":"So, yeah, the droids are taking our jobs,"},{"time":782471,"text":"but focusing on that fact\nmisses the point entirely."},{"time":786066,"text":"The point is that then we\nare freed up to do other things,"},{"time":789590,"text":"and what we're going to do,\nI am very confident,"},{"time":791901,"text":"what we're going to do is reduce poverty"},{"time":794441,"text":"and drudgery and misery around the world."},{"time":796934,"text":"I'm very confident we're going to learn\nto live more lightly on the planet,"},{"time":800963,"text":"and I am extremely confident\nthat what we're going to do"},{"time":804412,"text":"with our new digital tools"},{"time":805811,"text":"is going to be so profound\nand so beneficial"},{"time":808827,"text":"that it's going to make a mockery\nout of everything that came before."},{"time":812335,"text":"I'm going to leave the last word"},{"time":813915,"text":"to a guy who had a front-row seat\nfor digital progress,"},{"time":816593,"text":"our old friend Ken Jennings."},{"time":818189,"text":"I'm with him; I'm going to echo his words:"},{"time":820456,"text":"\"I, for one, welcome our new\ncomputer overlords.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":823396,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":824501,"text":"Thanks very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":826009,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}